FBIS4-30059 "dreas121_a_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-121 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Hata Suggests Readiness To Resign Hata Suggests Readiness To Resign OW2306085394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0848 GMT 23 Jun 94 OW2306085394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 23 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata Thursday suggested he is ready to resign along with his entire cabinet if the current talks between his ruling coalition and the Social Democratic Party call for the step. "I would like to leave (everything), including the issue of my resignation, to the decision of the talks," he said at a press conference.
